        <p>Most men over 40 need at least 0.5–0.6g per pound of bodyweight per day to protect muscle — and closer to 0.7–0.8g per pound to stay strong and active. For a 180-pound man, that's roughly 90–145g per day. Most men are currently getting less than half that.</p>
